text:
Some quick notes on combat: If you move too much it makes dodging difficult. Position yourself well and don't move too much from the good spots. Don't let enemies get behind you, round them up. You saw the Cuman friendly fire his buddy? That's why. Walking into an enemy initiates an animation that is largely governed by your stats vs theirs. Early on you will lose this clinch, later you will win it a lot. Don't get greedy with stamina, keep your armor and weapons in good shape.

For skills, make sure your equipment matches. I personally invest heavily in Longsword because it's a very powerful and versatile weapon with strong attack skills. Grind your sword skill a bit and you will start demolishing this game's combat. It's most difficult in the early game. Once you've got a brigandine or plate armor you'll really be doing well.
